main event: A radar sighting of a large para-glowing object was reported near Pendleton, Oregon on 9/8/60.
interesting points: The object was characterized as green or yellow and was observed moving at a speed of 30-40 mph., The object was lost due to radar ground clutter after approximately 15 minutes., The sighting was only recorded via radar, with no visual observations made., The incident was part of the documented investigations of Project Blue Book., Further reports indicate similar sightings of luminous objects in the sky.
sighted object: large green or yellow para-glowing object
